<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3000] Add ShutdownHook to YARN CLI to prevent lingering sessions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3000</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Submitting a job via&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;bin/flink run -m yarn-cluster ...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and terminating the client can lead to lingering YARN sessions allocating cluster resources.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was reported by a user.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;1) One starts a flink job in the yarn mode
2) He sees that containers are not allocated since cluster is busy
3) Presses Ctrl+C
4) An &#8220;empty&#8221; flink session remains in the cluster although the Flink didn&#8217;t print that &#8220;you can track your application on the X URL&#8221;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
